<br>
Wow, what a difference.<br>
<br>
C'mon people. Let's stop this stupid argument (and yes, sorry about my reply. I'm a hot head. Ok? Sorry y'all.)<br>
<br>
But am I the only one who sees the irony in this?? I mean, every pure caster class has a GOOD mana regen spell, except mages. Now even a hybrid is going to have a good mana regen spell, and we (mages), as usual, are getting crap spells. I mean, I can really see the use in the veil of invisibility (or whatever it's called), cuz lets face it, we all hate using Invis, and see the message &quot;You feel like you're about to appear&quot; when you must not appear at any costs. That's a good spell, but c'mon, every other class is getting at least 2 or 3 good spells that I wouldn't mind having it.<br>
<br>
We're masters of the elements. How hard would it be for a mage to control the earth bellow someone's feet and root them?? It's simple things like that that makes me raging mad. It's obviously Verant hates mages (have you ever noticed that there are not even one GM that plays a mage??). <br>
<br>
Really, I get extremelly angry because of this. It's not the point if our pets are better than others (which they are). But lets examine who should have a pet. Mages can summon pets. So that's ok. Necro's can animate the dead. So that's ok too. Chanter are masters of illusions. How does that make them SUMMON a pet?? And now wizards. C'mon, isn't it enough that they have the best nukes in the game?? Isn't it enough that their very powerful nukes have really fast casting times?? Isn't it enough that they can port?? How cheap is that?? Cheapness is the main reason why I will never ever start playing a Wizard or a Druid, and I tell that straight up to any druid and wiz that get in my face. They're cheap and that's that.<br>
<br>
Now druids are, well, simply put, pathetic. I hate their guts with a passion. Let's see here, they have: Fear (on animals), root, ports, 2nd best nukes in game (sad but true), powerful dots, snare, damage shields, healing spells, buffs, harmony, etc. Am I missing something? I probably am, since they have every frigging spell on the game. Oh yeah, they also get pets. WEAK pets, but nonetheless.<br>
<br>
You guys gotta face it, mages keep getting screwed over and over again, and the last thing I wanna see is someone kissing Verant's ass, and saying how &quot;GREAT&quot; the mage class is, cuz again, lets face it. We used to be great in terms of power, but not anymore. <br>
<br>
::sigh::<br>
<br>
I remember playing this game back in day, where I could beat almost any class with my mage. Now I can count with one hand the classes we can beat in duels.... and I'd still have a few fingers left. This totally sucks. Mages should be one of the strongest classes in the game (and not because I play a mage, cuz I also play a Necro, who is higher lvl than my mage btw), but when you think about it, they really should be the powerhouses in the game. We're the MASTERS of all 4 elements, how many other classes can say that?? Too bad they're almost all stronger than us. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umisstyofprexus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Missty of Prexus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/01 9:21:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=135.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: lvl 54 Mage wants to Rant about Mages </span><hr size=1> Thanks Esper for starting this.  A lot of things have been running through my mind lately.  I will never stop playing my mage.  I'll quit EQ first.  But here are my rants.<br>
